There's so much we can teach you. We've
improved the lives of savages all over.

525
00:38:42,720 --> 00:38:43,680
Savages?

526
00:38:43,922 --> 00:38:45,822
Not that you're a savage.

527
00:38:46,191 --> 00:38:47,651
- Just my people.
- No.

528
00:38:47,926 --> 00:38:50,556
Listen, that's not what I meant.
Let me explain.

529
00:38:51,029 --> 00:38:53,839
- Let go!
- No. I'm not letting you leave.

530
00:38:55,633 --> 00:38:57,363
Look, don't do this.

531
00:38:57,669 --> 00:39:00,799
Savage is just a word, you know?

532
00:39:01,339 --> 00:39:04,558
A term for...
people who are uncivilized.

533
00:39:05,109 --> 00:39:06,038
Like me.

534
00:39:06,244 --> 00:39:09,754
When I say uncivilized,
what I mean is...

535
00:39:19,858 --> 00:39:22,859
What you mean is... not like you.

536
00:39:22,861 --> 00:39:23,290
What you mean is... not like you.

537
00:39:23,428 --> 00:39:26,417
You think I'm an ignorant savage

538
00:39:26,931 --> 00:39:28,951
And you've been so many places

539
00:39:29,300 --> 00:39:31,410
I guess it must be so

540
00:39:31,769 --> 00:39:33,988
But still, l cannot see

541
00:39:34,372 --> 00:39:37,332
If the savage one is me

542
00:39:37,842 --> 00:39:42,622
How can there be so much
that you don't know

543
00:39:43,748 --> 00:39:48,198
You don't know

544
00:39:56,794 --> 00:40:01,154
You think you own
whatever land you land on

545
00:40:01,833 --> 00:40:05,733
The earth is just
a dead thing you can claim

546
00:40:06,371 --> 00:40:10,211
But I know every rock
and tree and creature

547
00:40:10,808 --> 00:40:14,848
Has a life, has a spirit
has a name

548
00:40:15,613 --> 00:40:19,482
You think the only people
who are people

549
00:40:20,118 --> 00:40:23,778
Are the people
who look and think like you

550
00:40:24,389 --> 00:40:28,019
But if you walk
the footsteps of a stranger

551
00:40:28,626 --> 00:40:32,816
You'll learn things
you never knew you never knew

552
00:40:33,464 --> 00:40:37,824
Have you ever heard the wolf cry
to the biue corn moon?

553
00:40:38,503 --> 00:40:42,043
Or ask the grinning bobcat
why he grinned?

554
00:40:42,640 --> 00:40:46,770
Can you sing with all the voices
of the mountain?

555
00:40:47,445 --> 00:40:51,605
Can you paint with alf the colors
of the wind?

556
00:40:52,283 --> 00:40:55,353
Can you paint with alf the colors

557
00:40:55,887 --> 00:40:59,107
Of the wind?

558
00:41:06,464 --> 00:41:09,944
Come run the hidden pine trails
of the forest

559
00:41:10,535 --> 00:41:14,134
Come taste the sun-sweet berries
of the earth

560
00:41:14,772 --> 00:41:18,142
Come roll in all the riches
all around you

561
00:41:18,710 --> 00:41:22,690
And for once, never wonder
what they're worth

562
00:41:23,348 --> 00:41:26,858
The rainstorm and the river
are my brothers

563
00:41:27,418 --> 00:41:31,488
The heron and the otter
are my friends

564
00:41:32,156 --> 00:41:35,696
And we are aif connected to each other

565
00:41:36,260 --> 00:41:40,570
In a circle in a hoop
that never ends

566
00:41:41,232 --> 00:41:44,952
How high does the sycamore grow?

567
00:41:45,570 --> 00:41:47,240
If you cut it down

568
00:41:47,538 --> 00:41:50,998
Then you'll never know

569
00:41:51,542 --> 00:41:54,761
And you'll never hear the wolf cry

570
00:41:55,279 --> 00:41:57,469
To the blue corn moon

571
00:41:57,882 --> 00:42:01,362
For whether we are white
or copper-skinned

572
00:42:01,986 --> 00:42:05,856
We need to sing with all the voices
of the mountain

573
00:42:06,457 --> 00:42:11,027
We need to paint with alf the colors
of the wind

574
00:42:11,796 --> 00:42:14,375
You can own the earth, and still

575
00:42:14,799 --> 00:42:17,929
Alf you'll own is earth until

576
00:42:18,436 --> 00:42:20,606
You can paint

577
00:42:20,972 --> 00:42:23,662
With aif the colors

578
00:42:24,108 --> 00:42:27,418
Of the

579
00:42:27,979 --> 00:42:31,879
Wind

580
00:42:48,766 --> 00:42:50,226
What is it?

581
00:42:50,501 --> 00:42:53,691
The drums.
They mean trouble.

582
00:42:54,238 --> 00:42:56,488
I shouldn't be here.

583
00:42:56,908 --> 00:42:58,548
- [ want to see you again.
- lL can't.

584
00:42:58,843 --> 00:43:00,593
- Please, don't leave.
- I'm sorry.

585
00:43:04,115 --> 00:43:05,895
l have to go.

586
00:43:16,427 --> 00:43:18,537
All right!
This one's ready to hoist!

587
00:43:18,930 --> 00:43:21,100
Two on each side.
Ready now? Push!

588
00:43:21,499 --> 00:43:22,959
Watch it! It's slipping.

589
00:43:23,234 --> 00:43:25,924
Come on, lads, it's only
a little picket fence.

590
00:43:26,370 --> 00:43:28,359
- Steady!
- There you go.

591
00:43:28,706 --> 00:43:30,846
That'll keep everything out.

592
00:43:33,311 --> 00:43:35,501
- Something wrong, John?
- What?

593
00:43:35,880 --> 00:43:39,660
- You've been quiet the last few days.
- He's mad he missed all the action.

594
00:43:40,251 --> 00:43:43,211
Don't worry. You'll get your chance
to deal with the Indians.

595
00:43:43,721 --> 00:43:47,061
We'll take care of them,
like we did last time.

596
00:43:47,592 --> 00:43:49,762
We shot ourselves an injun

597
00:43:50,128 --> 00:43:51,738
Or maybe two or three

598
00:43:52,029 --> 00:43:54,279
All right, you howling nutter,
get to work.

599
00:43:54,665 --> 00:43:56,775
Come on, Ben.
It's just a little fun.

600
00:43:57,168 --> 00:43:59,568
Sure! We're having loads of fun, right?

601
00:43:59,971 --> 00:44:01,961
Look at us. No gold, no food,

602
00:44:02,340 --> 00:44:06,260
while Ratcliffe sits up in his tent
all day, happy as a clam.

603
00:44:06,878 --> 00:44:08,988
I'm doomed!

604
00:44:09,347 --> 00:44:12,857
I should be wallowing in riches by now,
and I haven't found as much as a speck.

605
00:44:13,417 --> 00:44:17,667
Think. Think!
It's got to be around here somewhere.

606
00:44:19,657 --> 00:44:20,967
Where could it be?

607
00:44:22,760 --> 00:44:27,620
I've mined the forests and the hills
and the swamps... and nothing!

608
00:44:31,002 --> 00:44:33,991
Why can't I find it?
What am I overlooking?

609
00:44:35,840 --> 00:44:37,860


610
00:44:38,242 --> 00:44:39,642
l made it myself!

611
00:44:39,944 --> 00:44:41,754
Take that silly...

612
00:44:42,079 --> 00:44:44,479
Of course. The Indians.

613
00:44:44,916 --> 00:44:48,016
Wiggins, why do you think
those insolent heathens attacked us?

614
00:44:48,553 --> 00:44:51,453
We invaded their land, cut down
their trees and dug up their earth?

615
00:44:51,923 --> 00:44:53,732
It's the gold!
They have it,

616
00:44:54,058 --> 00:44:56,278
and they don't want us
to take it from them.

617
00:44:56,694 --> 00:44:59,854
I'll just have to
take it by force, won't I?

618
00:45:02,300 --> 00:45:04,790
You there!
Where's Captain Smith?

619
00:45:05,203 --> 00:45:09,243
- Well, he's... gone.
- Aye. Your singing scared him off.

620
00:45:09,907 --> 00:45:12,927
- Go get him, for heaven's sake!
- What if we run into the Indians?

621
00:45:13,444 --> 00:45:15,933
That's what guns are for.

622
00:45:16,347 --> 00:45:18,157
Now arm yourselves
and get moving!

623
00:45:43,975 --> 00:45:45,674
Pocahontas.

624
00:45:46,043 --> 00:45:48,533
You should be inside the village.

625
00:45:48,980 --> 00:45:50,320
We'll be all right.

626
00:45:50,615 --> 00:45:53,365
We're gathering food for
when the warriors arrive.

627
00:45:53,818 --> 00:45:54,748
Don't go far.

628
00:45:54,986 --> 00:45:57,975
- Now is not the time to be running off.
- Yes, Father.

629
00:45:59,957 --> 00:46:03,647
When I see you wear that necklace,
you look just like your mother.

630
00:46:05,096 --> 00:46:06,436
I miss her.

631
00:46:06,697 --> 00:46:08,717
But she is still with us.

632
00:46:09,100 --> 00:46:11,210
Whenever the wind moves
through the trees,

633
00:46:11,602 --> 00:46:13,241
I feel her presence.

634
00:46:13,537 --> 00:46:15,937
Our people look to her
for wisdom and strength.

635
00:46:16,340 --> 00:46:18,680
Someday, they will look to you as well.

636
00:46:19,076 --> 00:46:20,686
I would be honored by that.

637
00:46:21,045 --> 00:46:23,505
You shouldn't be
out here alone.

638
00:46:23,914 --> 00:46:26,844
- I'll send for Kocoum.
- All right, what is it?

639
00:46:27,351 --> 00:46:28,721
- What?
- You're hiding something.

640
00:46:29,020 --> 00:46:30,690
I'm not hiding anything.

641
00:46:30,988 --> 00:46:32,828
Pocahontas, you can tell me.
I promise.

642
00:46:33,190 --> 00:46:36,730
I won't tell anyone...
Pocahontas, look!

643
00:46:40,631 --> 00:46:43,821
- It's one of them! I'm going to get...
- What are you doing here?

644
00:46:44,368 --> 00:46:45,298
l had to see you again.

645
00:46:46,437 --> 00:46:49,187
Pocahontas!
Pocahontas!

646
00:46:49,640 --> 00:46:51,190
Please! Don't say anything.

647
00:46:51,509 --> 00:46:52,849
Quick! This way!

648
00:46:53,144 --> 00:46:54,484
- But...
- Nakoma.

649
00:46:54,745 --> 00:46:58,665
- Where is Pocahontas?
- [haven't seen her.

650
00:46:59,317 --> 00:47:01,897
Pocahontas can't keep running off.

651
00:47:02,353 --> 00:47:04,053
It's dangerous out there.

652
00:47:04,355 --> 00:47:07,135
Tell her that.
She listens to you.

653
00:47:10,161 --> 00:47:11,621
Sure she does.

654
00:47:27,845 --> 00:47:29,714
This place is incredible.

655
00:47:30,081 --> 00:47:32,891
To think we came all this way,
just to dig it up for gold.

656
00:47:33,351 --> 00:47:34,991
- Gold?
- Hey, Meeko.

657
00:47:35,319 --> 00:47:38,659
- What's gold?
- You know, it's yellow.

658
00:47:39,190 --> 00:47:41,060
It comes out of the ground.
It's valuable.

659
00:47:41,425 --> 00:47:43,095
Oh! Here, we have lots of it.

660
00:47:43,394 --> 00:47:45,383
Gold.

661
00:47:45,763 --> 00:47:49,543
No, no! Gold is this.

662
00:47:50,134 --> 00:47:51,914
There's nothing
like that around here.

663
00:47:52,236 --> 00:47:54,546
- No gold?
- Not that I've seen.

664
00:47:54,939 --> 00:47:57,339
All this way for nothing.

665
00:47:57,775 --> 00:48:00,205
Those boys are
in for a big surprise.

666
00:48:00,611 --> 00:48:02,661
- Will they leave?
- Some of them might.

667
00:48:05,349 --> 00:48:06,309
Will you go home?

668
00:48:06,517 --> 00:48:09,557
It's not like I have
much of a home to go back to.

669
00:48:10,054 --> 00:48:12,194
I've never
really belonged anywhere.

670
00:48:12,556 --> 00:48:14,516
You could belong here.

671
00:48:23,501 --> 00:48:25,251
What was that?

672
00:48:25,569 --> 00:48:29,288
- Did you see something?
- No. I just...

673
00:48:29,907 --> 00:48:32,657
..1 didn't see anything.
Did I?

674
00:48:33,110 --> 00:48:34,510
Look again.

675
00:48:35,846 --> 00:48:38,426
Let it break upon you

676
00:48:38,883 --> 00:48:43,042
Like a wave upon the sand

677
00:48:44,422 --> 00:48:46,972
Hello, John Smith.

678
00:48:47,391 --> 00:48:50,001
Pocahontas, that tree is talking to me.

679
00:48:50,461 --> 00:48:52,241
Then you should talk back.

680
00:48:52,596 --> 00:48:54,266
Don't be frightened, young man.

681
00:48:54,598 --> 00:48:56,908
My bark is worse than my bite.

682
00:48:58,869 --> 00:49:02,029
- Say something.
- What do you say to a tree?

683
00:49:02,540 --> 00:49:04,560
Anything you want.

684
00:49:07,945 --> 00:49:09,345
So...

685
00:49:09,613 --> 00:49:11,752
Come closer, John Smith.

686
00:49:13,350 --> 00:49:17,190
He has a good soul.
And he's handsome, too!

687
00:49:17,788 --> 00:49:20,718
- [like her.
- [knew you would.

688
00:49:21,192 --> 00:49:22,152
Smith!

689
00:49:22,359 --> 00:49:24,288
Smith, where are you, mate?

690
00:49:24,662 --> 00:49:26,942
- We can't let them see us.
- Quick! Over here.

691
00:49:27,364 --> 00:49:30,734
This place gives me the creeps.
Savages could be hiding anywhere.

692
00:49:31,268 --> 00:49:34,988
If you spot one, don't ask questions.
Just shoot.

693
00:49:37,541 --> 00:49:39,121
Watch your feet, you big oaf!

694
00:49:39,410 --> 00:49:40,990
It wasn't me! It was the tree.

695
00:49:41,278 --> 00:49:44,437
Of course! The tree just felt like
lifting its roots...

696
00:49:48,185 --> 00:49:49,445
Let's get out of here.

697
00:49:51,922 --> 00:49:53,972
- Run!
- But what about Smith?

698
00:49:54,325 --> 00:49:56,814
He's a big lad!
He can take care of himself!

699
00:49:57,228 --> 00:49:58,308
Glad you're on our side.

700
00:49:58,529 --> 00:50:01,189
There's still some snap
in these old vines.

701
00:50:01,632 --> 00:50:04,122
I better get back before they
send the camp after me.

702
00:50:04,535 --> 00:50:07,815
- When willl see you again?
- Meet me tonight, right here.

703
00:50:13,511 --> 00:50:17,671
Well! l haven't had this much
excitement in 200 years.

704
00:50:18,349 --> 00:50:21,189
What am I doing?
I shouldn't be seeing him again.

705
00:50:21,685 --> 00:50:23,235
I mean,
I want to see him again.

706
00:50:23,554 --> 00:50:26,214
Who wouldn't?
I want to see him again.

707
00:50:26,657 --> 00:50:30,117
But still, something inside
is telling me it's the right thing.

708
00:50:30,694 --> 00:50:32,124
Perhaps it's your dream.

709
00:50:32,429 --> 00:50:36,849
My dream? Do you think he's the one
the spinning arrow was pointing to?

710
00:50:46,744 --> 00:50:48,204
The warriors are here!

711
00:51:00,124 --> 00:51:02,493
Pocahontas, are you crazy?
What were you doing?

712
00:51:02,927 --> 00:51:04,187
- There you are!
- Kocoum!

713
00:51:04,461 --> 00:51:08,060
Look at them! Now we have enough
warriors to destroy those white demons!

714
00:51:10,501 --> 00:51:14,311
Now that we are joined by our brothers,
we will defeat this enemy.

715
00:51:22,413 --> 00:51:24,053
Father, I need to speak with you.

716
00:51:24,348 --> 00:51:26,598
Not now, my daughter.
The council is gathering.

717
00:51:26,984 --> 00:51:29,944
We don't have to fight them.
There must be a better way.

718
00:51:30,421 --> 00:51:32,821
Sometimes our paths are chosen for us.

719
00:51:33,257 --> 00:51:35,537
But maybe we should try
talking to them.

720
00:51:35,960 --> 00:51:37,360
They do not want to talk.

721
00:51:37,661 --> 00:51:40,851
But if one of them did want to talk,
you would listen to him, wouldn't you?

722
00:51:41,398 --> 00:51:43,128
- Pocahontas...
- Wouldn't you?

723
00:51:43,434 --> 00:51:47,244
Of course I would,
but it is not that simple.

724
00:51:47,838 --> 00:51:50,118
Nothing is simple anymore.

725
00:52:34,051 --> 00:52:36,161
Easy, Thomas, it's me.

726
00:52:37,488 --> 00:52:41,558
- Oh, John! I could've killed you.
- Not aiming like that, you couldn't.

727
00:52:42,226 --> 00:52:44,886
Keep both eyes open when you shoot.
You'll see twice as well.

728
00:52:46,864 --> 00:52:48,204
Smith! There you are!

729
00:52:48,465 --> 00:52:50,015
We were looking
all over for you.

730
00:52:50,300 --> 00:52:53,050
Smith! Where have you been?

731
00:52:53,504 --> 00:52:55,844
Il was out scouting
the terrain, sir.

732
00:52:56,240 --> 00:52:58,459
Then you must know
the Indians' whereabouts.

733
00:52:58,876 --> 00:53:01,216
- We'll need that for the battle.
- What battle?

734
00:53:01,612 --> 00:53:04,192
We will eliminate these savages
once and for all.

735
00:53:04,615 --> 00:53:05,875
No! You can't do that!

736
00:53:06,116 --> 00:53:08,576
Oh, can't I?

737
00:53:08,986 --> 00:53:11,386
We don't have to fight them.

738
00:53:11,822 --> 00:53:13,522
- What's gotten into you?
- [met one.

739
00:53:13,824 --> 00:53:15,874
- You what?
- Asavage?

740
00:53:16,260 --> 00:53:18,190
They're not savages.
They can help us.

741
00:53:18,562 --> 00:53:21,172
They know the land. They know how
to navigate the rivers.

742
00:53:22,533 --> 00:53:25,143
- And look. It's food.
- What is it?

743
00:53:25,569 --> 00:53:28,699
- It's better than hardtack and gruel.
- like gruel.

744
00:53:29,239 --> 00:53:31,109
They don't want to feed us,
you ninnies!

745
00:53:31,442 --> 00:53:34,052
They want to kill us!
All of us!

746
00:53:34,545 --> 00:53:37,095
They've got our gold,
and they'll do anything to keep it!

747
00:53:37,514 --> 00:53:38,804
But there is no gold.

748
00:53:39,083 --> 00:53:40,783
No gold?

749
00:53:41,085 --> 00:53:44,865
And I suppose your little
Indian friend told you this?

750
00:53:45,456 --> 00:53:46,716
Yes.

751
00:53:46,957 --> 00:53:50,176
Lies! All of it!
Murderous thieves.

752
00:53:50,694 --> 00:53:52,594
There's no room for their kind
in society.

753
00:53:52,963 --> 00:53:54,013
But this is their land!

754
00:53:54,264 --> 00:53:57,254
This is my land!
l make the laws here.

755
00:53:57,768 --> 00:54:01,518
And I say anyone who so much
as looks at an Indian

756
00:54:02,106 --> 00:54:06,416
without killing him on sight
will be tried for treason and hanged.

757
00:54:12,382 --> 00:54:13,752
Pocahontas!

758
00:54:14,017 --> 00:54:15,506
- Nakoma.
- Don't go out there.

759
00:54:15,819 --> 00:54:18,689
I lied for you once.
Don't ask me to do it again.

760
00:54:19,189 --> 00:54:20,529
I have to do this.

761
00:54:20,824 --> 00:54:22,694
- He's one of them!
- You don't know him.

762
00:54:23,026 --> 00:54:25,576
If you go, you'll be turning
your back on your own people.

763
00:54:25,996 --> 00:54:28,046
I'm trying to help my people.

764
00:54:28,432 --> 00:54:31,361
Pocahontas, please.
You're my best friend.

765
00:54:31,835 --> 00:54:33,295
I don't want you to get hurt.

766
00:54:33,570 --> 00:54:36,910
- L won't. [ know what I'm doing.
- Pocahontas, no!

767
00:54:44,081 --> 00:54:46,631
Ratcliffe wouldn't take us
around the world for nothing.

768
00:54:47,084 --> 00:54:50,073
But what if Smith is right?
What if there is no gold?

769
00:54:50,554 --> 00:54:53,424
If you ask me, Ratcliffe's been
lying to us since we left London.

770
00:54:53,891 --> 00:54:55,441
Listen to you,
you bunch of idiots.

771
00:54:55,726 --> 00:54:57,836
Those savages didn't
attack us for nothing.

772
00:54:58,228 --> 00:54:59,688
They're hiding something.

773
00:54:59,963 --> 00:55:03,003
If they do have the gold,
l reckon we'll have to fight them.

774
00:55:03,500 --> 00:55:05,750
Either too hot or too cold.

775
00:55:06,170 --> 00:55:09,300
l haven't been comfortable
since we got here.

776
00:55:09,840 --> 00:55:12,090
Me, too. I'm itching a lot.

777
00:55:19,416 --> 00:55:21,586
- Follow him.
- Yes, Governor.

778
00:55:21,952 --> 00:55:24,062
l want to know where
he's sneaking off to.

779
00:55:24,488 --> 00:55:27,067
- Yes, sir.
- If you happen to see any Indians...

780
00:55:28,425 --> 00:55:29,795
.-Shoot them.

781
00:55:33,597 --> 00:55:36,147
And, Thomas,
you've been a slipshod sailor

782
00:55:36,600 --> 00:55:38,560
and a poor excuse for a soldier.

783
00:55:38,936 --> 00:55:41,106
Don't disappoint me again.

784
00:55:50,981 --> 00:55:53,201
- Kocoum.
- What is it?

785
00:55:53,617 --> 00:55:57,837
- It's Pocahontas.
- What's wrong? Is she all right?

786
00:56:00,457 --> 00:56:02,156
I think she's in trouble.

787
00:56:06,964 --> 00:56:09,624
The earth is trembling, child.
What's happened?

788
00:56:10,100 --> 00:56:11,360
The warriors are here.

789
00:56:11,635 --> 00:56:14,265
- Pocahontas.
- John!

790
00:56:14,705 --> 00:56:17,895
Listen to me. My men are planning
to attack your people.

791
00:56:18,408 --> 00:56:19,548
You've got to warn them.

792
00:56:19,810 --> 00:56:21,860
Maybe it's not too late
to stop this.

793
00:56:22,212 --> 00:56:24,082
You have to talk to my father.

794
00:56:24,448 --> 00:56:26,638
Pocahontas, talking isn't
going to do any good.

795
00:56:27,017 --> 00:56:28,537
I've talked to my men,

796
00:56:28,886 --> 00:56:31,256
but everything
about this land has them spooked.

797
00:56:35,659 --> 00:56:37,829
That's the strangest creature
I've ever seen!

798
00:56:42,165 --> 00:56:43,595
Percy?

799
00:56:46,303 --> 00:56:48,583
- Easy, Percy! Come here!
- Meeko, come back!

800
00:56:49,006 --> 00:56:51,435
Once two sides want to fight,
nothing can stop them.

801
00:56:51,842 --> 00:56:54,712
- Come here both of you!
- It's all right. He's a friend.

802
00:56:55,178 --> 00:56:56,258
Bad! Bad dog! Sit!

803
00:56:58,715 --> 00:57:01,145
- What are you doing? Meeko!
- Percy, get back here!

804
00:57:01,585 --> 00:57:05,065
- What are you doing? Stop that!
- All right, that's enough!

805
00:57:12,396 --> 00:57:14,646
It's enough to make your sap boil.

806
00:57:16,400 --> 00:57:20,300
Now then, there's something
l want to show you. Look!

807
00:57:23,941 --> 00:57:27,571
- The ripples.
- What about them?

808
00:57:28,178 --> 00:57:32,158
So small at first,
then look how they grow.

809
00:57:34,017 --> 00:57:36,357
But someone has to start them.

810
00:57:36,753 --> 00:57:38,713
They're not going to listen to us.

811
00:57:39,056 --> 00:57:42,836
Young man, sometimes the right path
is not the easiest one.

812
00:57:43,427 --> 00:57:45,007
Don't you see?

813
00:57:45,295 --> 00:57:49,135
Only when the fighting
stops can you be together.

814
00:57:53,637 --> 00:57:56,037
All right. Let's go talk to your father.

815
00:58:32,509 --> 00:58:34,529
Kocoum, no!

816
00:58:41,318 --> 00:58:42,808
Kocoum!

817
00:58:46,089 --> 00:58:47,288
Leave him alone!

818
00:59:03,774 --> 00:59:05,674
Kocoum, stop!

819
00:59:08,178 --> 00:59:10,167
Both eyes open.

820
00:59:17,988 --> 00:59:20,917
- Thomas!
- Is he...

821
00:59:21,391 --> 00:59:23,031
You killed him.

822
00:59:23,326 --> 00:59:25,026
- [ thought that...
- Get away from him!

823
00:59:25,328 --> 00:59:28,258
- Pocahontas, it won't help! He was...
- He killed him!

824
00:59:31,568 --> 00:59:34,998
Thomas, get out of here!
Get out of here!

825
01:00:39,469 --> 01:00:40,699
Who did this?

826
01:00:40,937 --> 01:00:42,897
Pocahontas was out in the woods.

827
01:00:43,240 --> 01:00:45,609
Kocoum went to find her
and this man attacked them.

828
01:00:47,777 --> 01:00:50,327
Your weapons are strong,

829
01:00:50,747 --> 01:00:52,647
but now our anger is stronger.

830
01:00:53,016 --> 01:00:55,976
- At sunrise, he'll be the first to die!
- But, Father!

831
01:00:56,453 --> 01:00:59,673
I told you to stay in the village.

832
01:01:00,190 --> 01:01:01,830
You disobeyed me.

833
01:01:02,125 --> 01:01:03,765
You have shamed your father!

834
01:01:04,094 --> 01:01:05,644
I was only trying to help.

835
01:01:05,929 --> 01:01:09,469
Because of your foolishness,
Kocoum is dead!

836
01:01:10,033 --> 01:01:11,673
Take him away!

837
01:01:26,483 --> 01:01:28,503
Kocoum was just coming
to protect me.

838
01:01:28,885 --> 01:01:30,555
Pocahontas...

839
01:01:30,854 --> 01:01:32,524
..l sent Kocoum after you.

840
01:01:34,291 --> 01:01:36,431
Il was worried about you.

841
01:01:36,860 --> 01:01:38,880
I thought I was doing
the right thing.

842
01:01:39,262 --> 01:01:41,782
All this happened because of me.

843
01:01:42,199 --> 01:01:44,919
And now I'll never see
John Smith again.

844
01:01:47,470 --> 01:01:48,839
Come with me.

845
01:01:53,510 --> 01:01:57,200
Pocahontas wants to look into the eyes
of the man who killed Kocoum.

846
01:02:00,517 --> 01:02:02,006
Be quick.

847
01:02:20,437 --> 01:02:22,017
Pocahontas.

848
01:02:24,641 --> 01:02:26,541
I'm so sorry.

849
01:02:26,876 --> 01:02:27,986
For what? This?

850
01:02:28,245 --> 01:02:30,355
I've gotten out of
worse scrapes than this.

851
01:02:30,747 --> 01:02:32,207
Can't think of any now, but...

852
01:02:32,482 --> 01:02:34,152
It would've been better
if we'd never met.

853
01:02:34,484 --> 01:02:36,214
None of this would've happened.

854
01:02:36,519 --> 01:02:38,328
Pocahontas, look at me.

855
01:02:38,722 --> 01:02:43,882
I'd rather die tomorrow than live
a hundred years without knowing you.

856
01:02:45,528 --> 01:02:48,368
- Pocahontas.
- L can't leave you.

857
01:02:48,832 --> 01:02:50,092
You never will.

858
01:02:50,333 --> 01:02:54,523
No matter what happens to me,
I'll always be with you. Forever.

859
01:03:08,084 --> 01:03:09,924
Help! Somebody help!

860
01:03:10,253 --> 01:03:11,363
Help!

861
01:03:11,588 --> 01:03:13,048
Easy, lad. What is it?

862
01:03:13,356 --> 01:03:14,786
It's Smith! They got him!

863
01:03:15,058 --> 01:03:17,108
- Who got him?
- The savages!

864
01:03:17,460 --> 01:03:19,010
Captured him!
Dragged him off!

865
01:03:19,296 --> 01:03:20,725
- Where'd they take him?
- North.

866
01:03:20,997 --> 01:03:22,926
- How many were there?
- At least a dozen.

867
01:03:23,266 --> 01:03:25,166
Filthy beasts!

868
01:03:25,535 --> 01:03:28,904
It's perfect, Wiggins! I couldn't
have planned this better myself.

869
01:03:29,472 --> 01:03:32,102
The gold is as good as mine.

870
01:03:32,542 --> 01:03:34,942
We've got to save him!
He'd do the same for any of us.

871
01:03:35,378 --> 01:03:37,548
Thomas is right!
We've got to do something.

872
01:03:37,914 --> 01:03:38,981
And so we shall. I told you those
savages couldn't be trusted.

873
01:03:38,982 --> 01:03:42,172
And so we shall. I told you those
savages couldn't be trusted.

874
01:03:42,719 --> 01:03:45,469
Smith tried to befriend them,
look what they've done to him!

875
01:03:45,922 --> 01:03:49,462
But now I say it's time to
rescue our courageous comrade.

876
01:03:50,060 --> 01:03:52,020
At daybreak, we attack!

877
01:03:53,863 --> 01:03:56,792
What can you expect
From filthy little heathens?

878
01:03:57,267 --> 01:04:00,017
Here's what you get
When races are diverse

879
01:04:00,470 --> 01:04:02,020
Their skin's a hellish red

880
01:04:02,305 --> 01:04:03,674
They're only good when dead

881
01:04:03,940 --> 01:04:06,160
They're vermin as I said
And worse

882
01:04:06,543 --> 01:04:09,033
They're savages, savages

883
01:04:09,446 --> 01:04:10,756
Barely even human

884
01:04:11,047 --> 01:04:12,357
Savages, savages

885
01:04:12,615 --> 01:04:14,104
Drive them from our shore!

886
01:04:14,417 --> 01:04:15,757
They're not like you and me

887
01:04:16,052 --> 01:04:17,542
Which means they must be evil

888
01:04:17,821 --> 01:04:20,341
We must sound the drums of war

889
01:04:20,757 --> 01:04:22,427
They're savages, savages

890
01:04:22,759 --> 01:04:24,429
Dirty shrieking devils

891
01:04:24,728 --> 01:04:28,038
Now we sound the drums of war

892
01:04:33,169 --> 01:04:34,719
This is what we feared

893
01:04:35,004 --> 01:04:36,524
The paleface is a demon

894
01:04:36,873 --> 01:04:39,483
The only thing
they feel at all is greed

895
01:04:39,943 --> 01:04:41,553
Beneath that milky hide

896
01:04:41,878 --> 01:04:43,248
There's emptiness inside

897
01:04:43,546 --> 01:04:45,566
! wonder if they even bleed

898
01:04:45,915 --> 01:04:48,375
They're savages, savages

899
01:04:48,818 --> 01:04:50,128
Barely even human

900
01:04:50,387 --> 01:04:51,847
Savages, savages

901
01:04:52,155 --> 01:04:53,265
Killers at the core

902
01:04:53,490 --> 01:04:55,160
They're different from us

903
01:04:55,492 --> 01:04:57,102
Which means they can't be trusted

904
01:04:57,427 --> 01:04:59,947
We must sound the drums of war

905
01:05:00,363 --> 01:05:02,113
They're savages, savages

906
01:05:02,465 --> 01:05:03,895
First we deal with this one

907
01:05:04,167 --> 01:05:05,656
Then we sound the drums of war

908
01:05:05,969 --> 01:05:07,199
Savages, savages

909
01:05:07,470 --> 01:05:08,959
Let's go get a few, men!

910
01:05:09,239 --> 01:05:10,699
Savages, savages

911
01:05:11,007 --> 01:05:12,497
Now it's up to you, men!

912
01:05:12,776 --> 01:05:14,236
- Savages
- Savages

913
01:05:14,511 --> 01:05:16,000
Barely even human

914
01:05:16,312 --> 01:05:19,301
Now we sound the drums

915
01:05:19,816 --> 01:05:22,685
Of war

916
01:05:31,661 --> 01:05:34,151
They're going to kill him at sunrise.

917
01:05:34,564 --> 01:05:35,874
You have to stop them.

918
01:05:36,132 --> 01:05:39,322
- lL can't.
- Child, remember your dream.

919
01:05:39,836 --> 01:05:43,176
Il was wrong, Grandmother Willow.
I followed the wrong path.

920
01:05:43,706 --> 01:05:45,606
I feel so lost.

921
01:06:03,460 --> 01:06:04,980
The compass.

922
01:06:12,702 --> 01:06:15,012
The spinning arrow.

923
01:06:15,472 --> 01:06:17,402
It's the arrow from your dream!

924
01:06:17,774 --> 01:06:20,554
I was right!
It was pointing to him!

925
01:06:27,450 --> 01:06:28,410
Sunrise!

926
01:06:28,651 --> 01:06:30,201
It's not too late, child!

927
01:06:30,520 --> 01:06:33,860
Let the spirits of the earth
guide you!

928
01:06:35,492 --> 01:06:39,302
You know your path, child.
Now follow it!

929
01:06:43,600 --> 01:06:45,060
This will be the day

930
01:06:45,335 --> 01:06:47,325
Let's go, men!

931
01:06:48,271 --> 01:06:50,731
This will be the morning

932
01:06:51,140 --> 01:06:52,779
Bring out the prisoner!

933
01:06:53,676 --> 01:06:55,196
We will see them
dying in the dust

934
01:06:55,512 --> 01:06:56,622
1 don't know what I can do

935
01:06:56,846 --> 01:06:58,486
Still 1 know I've got to try

936
01:06:58,781 --> 01:07:00,211
Now we make them pay

937
01:07:00,483 --> 01:07:01,883
Eagle, help my feet to fly

938
01:07:02,151 --> 01:07:03,491
Now, without a warning

939
01:07:03,753 --> 01:07:05,333
Mountain, help my heart be great

940
01:07:05,622 --> 01:07:06,912
Now we leave them
blood and bone and rust

941
01:07:07,156 --> 01:07:10,496
- Spirits of the earth and sky
- It's them or us

942
01:07:11,060 --> 01:07:13,279
Please don't let it be too late

943
01:07:13,663 --> 01:07:15,773
They're a bunch of
Filthy, stinking savages

944
01:07:16,132 --> 01:07:17,242
- Savages
- Demons

945
01:07:17,467 --> 01:07:18,427
- Devils
- Kill them!

946
01:07:18,635 --> 01:07:19,925
- Savages
- Savages

947
01:07:20,169 --> 01:07:21,429
What are we waiting for?

948
01:07:21,671 --> 01:07:23,071
Destroy their evil race

949
01:07:23,339 --> 01:07:25,038
Until there's not a trace left

950
01:07:25,341 --> 01:07:30,321
How loud are the drums of war?

951
01:07:31,681 --> 01:07:34,871
Now we see what comes
of trying to be chums

952
01:07:35,418 --> 01:07:36,908
ls the death of all I love

953
01:07:37,186 --> 01:07:40,056
Carried in the drumming of

954
01:07:40,523 --> 01:07:41,983
- War
- No!

955
01:07:46,129 --> 01:07:46,227
If you kill him,
you'll have to kill me too.

956
01:07:46,229 --> 01:07:49,069
If you kill him,
you'll have to kill me too.

957
01:07:49,532 --> 01:07:51,552
Daughter, stand back.

958
01:07:51,935 --> 01:07:55,275
I won't! I love him, Father.

959
01:08:01,811 --> 01:08:03,451
Look around you.

960
01:08:03,780 --> 01:08:06,680
This is where the path
of hatred has brought us.

961
01:08:09,786 --> 01:08:11,926
This is the path I choose, Father.

962
01:08:12,322 --> 01:08:13,522
What will yours be?

963
01:08:48,224 --> 01:08:51,944
My daughter speaks
with a wisdom beyond her years.

964
01:08:52,562 --> 01:08:55,402
We have all come here
with anger in our hearts...

965
01:08:55,932 --> 01:08:58,541
..but she comes with
courage and understanding.

966
01:08:58,968 --> 01:09:03,127
From this day forward,
if there is to be more killing,

967
01:09:03,773 --> 01:09:06,023
it will not start with me.

968
01:09:09,412 --> 01:09:10,812
Release him.

969
01:09:29,265 --> 01:09:30,965
Now is our chance! Fire!

970
01:09:31,267 --> 01:09:32,846
- No.
- What?

971
01:09:33,136 --> 01:09:35,476
- They let him go!
- They don't want to fight!

972
01:09:35,904 --> 01:09:38,804
It's a trick,
don't you see? Fire!

973
01:09:44,113 --> 01:09:45,633
Fine! I'll settle this myself.

974
01:09:48,317 --> 01:09:49,397
No!

975
01:09:50,787 --> 01:09:51,837
John!

976
01:09:57,894 --> 01:09:58,794
You shot him!

977
01:09:58,995 --> 01:10:02,215
He stepped right into it!
It's his own fault!

978
01:10:02,765 --> 01:10:05,075
- Smith was right.
- We never should've listened to you.

979
01:10:05,468 --> 01:10:07,458
- Get the gun!
- Traitors!

980
01:10:07,804 --> 01:10:09,474
Unhand me!
I say, how dare you!

981
01:10:09,806 --> 01:10:11,476
Put him in chains!

982
01:10:11,774 --> 01:10:14,084
I'll see you all hanged for this!

983
01:10:14,477 --> 01:10:15,876
And gag him as well!

984
01:10:28,324 --> 01:10:29,723
Is he going to make it?

985
01:10:29,992 --> 01:10:31,742
The sooner he gets to England,
the better.

986
01:10:32,095 --> 01:10:33,555
Let's hope the wind is with him.

987
01:10:33,830 --> 01:10:36,019
- ls the ship ready yet?
- Any minute now.

988
01:10:36,432 --> 01:10:38,621
Just loading
the last bit of cargo.

989
01:10:42,572 --> 01:10:44,092
Untie me at once!

990
01:10:44,407 --> 01:10:46,337
I'll have your head for this!

991
01:10:46,743 --> 01:10:49,493
And he came so highly recommended.

992
01:10:58,788 --> 01:11:00,367
The ship's almost ready.

993
01:11:00,656 --> 01:11:03,146
We'd better get you on board.
We'll lose the tide.

994
01:11:03,559 --> 01:11:06,489
No, not yet.
She said she'd be here.

995
01:11:06,963 --> 01:11:08,362
Look.

996
01:11:35,491 --> 01:11:37,631
Going back is his only chance.

997
01:11:37,994 --> 01:11:40,103
He'll die if he stays here.

998
01:11:48,905 --> 01:11:50,394
Here.

999
01:11:50,706 --> 01:11:52,896
It's from
Grandmother Willow's bark.

1000
01:11:53,276 --> 01:11:54,976
It'll help with the pain.

1001
01:11:55,311 --> 01:11:58,210
What pain?
I've had worse pain than this.

1002
01:11:58,714 --> 01:12:01,234
Can't think of any
right now, but...

1003
01:12:08,424 --> 01:12:10,944
You are always welcome
among our people.

1004
01:12:11,360 --> 01:12:13,610
Thank you, my brother.

1005
01:12:17,033 --> 01:12:18,963
I thought you didn't like strangers.

1006
01:12:28,211 --> 01:12:29,991
My mother's necklace.

1007
01:12:34,150 --> 01:12:35,320
See ya, Percy.

1008
01:12:52,802 --> 01:12:54,031
Come with me?

1009
01:12:58,741 --> 01:13:00,911
You must choose your own path.

1010
01:13:16,926 --> 01:13:18,506
I'm needed here.

1011
01:13:20,196 --> 01:13:21,976
Then... I'll stay with you.

1012
01:13:22,298 --> 01:13:25,338
No. You have to go back.

1013
01:13:25,835 --> 01:13:28,325
- But I can't leave you.
- You never will.

1014
01:13:28,738 --> 01:13:32,488
No matter what happens,
I'll always be with you...

1015
01:13:34,110 --> 01:13:35,809
.. forever.

1016
01:14:01,837 --> 01:14:04,707
- Good luck, lad.
- Godspeed, John.

1017
01:14:18,321 --> 01:14:20,341
Weigh anchor!

